President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Nebraska and ordered federal aid to help with recovery efforts after severe storms, tornadoes, straight-line winds, and flooding occurred between June 14-21, 2014. The federal funding will be used to supplement state and local recovery efforts, as well as for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also be funded. Christian Van Alstyne has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.